"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-10-09-french-minister-ups-ante-eiffel-tower-olympic-rings-row\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS,\\u00a0France\\u00a0(AFP)- A row over the Olympics logo becoming a long-term feature of the Eiffel Tower has taken a fresh turn with a French government minister bidding to take de facto control over the monument away from the city of Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997960365322386, \"rank\": 0.00010207666932677589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9680101127868359, \"rank\": 0.016904459148091515, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 229, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.309604262496156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The popular landmark sported giant Olympic rings during this summer's Olympics and Paralympics.\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The capital's mayor Anne Hidalgo- encouraged by the popular success of the Games- said a version of the decoration should adorn the tower until the next Olympics in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999962498652454, \"rank\": 3.5934161205016915e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that proposal has polarised opinion in the French capital and at the highest level of state.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9680101127868359, \"rank\": 0.016904459148091515, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Already, it has been severely criticised by descendants of the tower's designer Gustave Eiffel, as well as conservation groups.\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustave Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of last month, workers removed the 30-tonne steel rings that were first installed in June between the first and second floors of the tower.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo has campaigned for lighter, less prominent, versions of the originals to be installed in their place.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But even this toned-down proposal is too much for sceptics, some of whom are also bitter political enemies of Hidalgo.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999990150172, \"rank\": 9.849901898478878e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Socialist mayor has riled opponents with ambitious pro-cycling and anti-car projects, as well as a recent decision to cut the speed limit on Paris's ring road, the Peripherique.\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.309604262496156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of her most prominent critics is right-wing politician, Rachida Dati, who as leader of the opposition in Paris city hall has often locked horns with Hidalgo.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}, {\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999991164259, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris city hall\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1464, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999990150172, \"rank\": 9.849901898478878e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having failed in a previous bid, she is expected to run for mayor again in 2026 at the next municipal election.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dati was last month reappointed Culture Minister in Prime Minister Michel Barnier's government, a position that gives her much influence over listed buildings and their protection.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Barnier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michel Barnier\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Barnier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Barnier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Tuesday, she announced that she had asked for the Eiffel Tower to become part of the state's top heritage list.\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If granted, that would, de facto, wrest control over work done on the tower from the city and her rival Hidalgo, placing it in the hands of the central government.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1988, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999990150172, \"rank\": 9.849901898478878e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dati told the daily Le Parisien that the tower's current status as an ordinary listed monument was no longer sufficient.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Parisien\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only its inclusion on the French state's top heritage list, reserved for sites of national importance, would offer \\\"true protection\\\", she argued.\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9680101127868359, \"rank\": 0.016904459148091515, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Any work done on a building or monument with full heritage status requires the approval of the regional prefect, who answers to the government, or other state-run agencies.\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Should Hidalgo refuse Dati's request that the tower be added to the state's top heritage list, Dati said she would make the change \\\"by force\\\".\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked about the initiative Tuesday, Hidalgo said the Eiffel Tower was already \\\"very, very well protected\\\".\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2671, \"end\": 2678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999990150172, \"rank\": 9.849901898478878e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dati's remarks also caused anger at SETE, the company running the Eiffel Tower, which is majority-owned by the city of Paris.\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.309604262496156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SETE president Jean-Francois Martins told AFP that the culture minister was entitled to ask for heritage status if a site was endangered.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 3007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999642025166, \"rank\": 2.2356786825779932e-08, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But that's not the case for the Eiffel Tower,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The company was embarking on the tower's \\\"most ambitious ever\\\" paint job, had renovated lifts and improved accessibility, he added.\", \"from\": 3066, \"to\": 3197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Martins accused Dati of using the Eiffel Tower \\\"to further her political aims\\\".\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3291, \"entities\": []}]}"